3_4 Expression analysis during MZT

Manuel Jara-Espejo

1 Introduction

This document describe the first screening we did on embryonic transcriptome during the MZT/ZGA. It is based on PolyA exon-based expression clusters that were then used to model how our other transcriptomic data behaved. We aimed to have a first approximation to the expression dynamics involving maternal products fate and zygotic activation onset.

knitr::opts_chunk$set(message=F,warning=F,echo=T)

2 Call TPM data, apply some filters and scale to allow posteriori clustering

exon_polya_toClust <- embryo_exon_polya_tpm %>% dplyr::select(- p19) %>% column_to_rownames(var = "gene_id") %>%
  filter(p3.5 + p4.4 + p4.8 >= 3 | p4.4 + p4.8 + p5.5 >= 3 | p4.8 + p5.5 + p6.5 >= 3 | p4.8 + p5.5 + p6.5 >= 3 |
           p5.5 + p6.5 + p8 >= 3 | p6.5 + p8 + p10 >= 3 | p8 + p10 + p10_24 >= 3) %>%
  drop_na() %>% mutate(across(where(is.numeric), ~log2(. + 1) )) # Data was initially named based on developmental %, changed later to time in hours

exon_polya_toClust_scaled <- t(scale(t(exon_polya_toClust)))
colnames(exon_polya_toClust) <- c('0-9hs','11hs','12hs','13-14hs','16hs','20hs','24hs','24-60hs')
exon_polya_toClust %>% head(5)

3.3 Clustering data

set.seed(20)
kClust <- kmeans(exon_polya_toClust_scaled, centers=6, nstart = 1000, iter.max = 20)

3.4 Plot clusters centroids

# function to find centroid in cluster i
clust.centroid = function(i, dat, clusters) {
  ind = (clusters == i)
  colMeans(dat[ind,])
}
kClustcentroids <- sapply(levels(factor(kClusters)), clust.centroid, exon_polya_toClust_scaled, kClusters)

#Plotting the centroids to see how they behave:
Kmolten <- melt(kClustcentroids)
colnames(Kmolten) <- c('sample','cluster','value')

p1 <- ggplot(Kmolten, aes(x=sample,y=value, group=cluster, colour=as.factor(cluster))) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line() +
  xlab("Time") +
  ylab("Expression") +
  labs(title= "Cluster Expression by Time",color = "Cluster")
p1

4 Heatmap of clusters

4.1 Merge orignal TPM counts and clustered data. Reorder based on cluster number

exon_polya_toClust2 <- cbind(exon_polya_toClust,kClust$cluster) %>%dplyr::rename("cluster" = "kClust$cluster" )
exon_polya_toClust2$cluster <- factor(exon_polya_toClust2$cluster ,levels = c(2,5,6,4,3,1))
o <- order(exon_polya_toClust2$cluster )
exon_polya_toClust2 <- exon_polya_toClust2[o, ]
exon_polya_toClust2 %>% head()

4.2 Plot heatmap

col  = colorRampPalette(c("darkslategray","red"))(20)
annotation_df = data.frame("Cluster" = as.character(exon_polya_toClust2$cluster))
rownames(annotation_df) <- rownames(exon_polya_toClust2)
get_my_colors <- colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(6, "Dark2")) #Function to select color based on number of unique clusters

mycolors <- get_my_colors(length(unique(annotation_df$Cluster)))
names(mycolors) <- factor(unique(annotation_df$Cluster))
names(mycolors) <- c("2","5","6","4","3","1") #Reorder
mycolors <- list(Cluster = mycolors)

p2 <- pheatmap(exon_polya_toClust2[,1:8], cluster_rows=F,cluster_cols=F,scale = "row",show_rownames = F,angle_col = 45,
               color = col,main = "",annotation_row = annotation_df,annotation_legend=F, 
               annotation_colors = mycolors,annotation_names_row =F,
               labels_col= c('0-9','11','12','13-14','16','20','24','24-60'),fontsize_col =8)

write.table(exon_polya_toClust2 %>% rownames_to_column(var = "gene_id") ,"embryo_exonCounts_clustered.txt",sep = "\t",quote = F,row.names = F ,col.names = T)

4.3 Get expression averaged pattern by cluster and plot

4.3.1 Exon PolyA RNA

#Reorder centroids data
Kmolten$cluster <- factor(Kmolten$cluster,levels = c(2,5,6,4,3,1))
Kmolten <- Kmolten[order(Kmolten$cluster), ]

#Data frame with text annotations(number of genes per cluster)
#exon_polya_toClust2$cluster %>% table()
dat_text <- data.frame(label = c("n = 1931", "n = 3650","n = 3048","n = 3792","n = 2443", "n = 1236"),cluster = factor(c(2,5,6,4,3,1), levels= c(2,5,6,4,3,1)))

p3 <- ggplot(Kmolten, aes(x=sample,y=value, group=cluster, colour=as.factor(cluster))) + 
  geom_point(shape = 18) + geom_line() +
  scale_colour_manual(values=c("#1B9E77","#D95F02","#7570B3","#E7298A","#66A61E","#E6AB02"))+
  labs(title= "",color = "black", y="Expression",x="") + facet_grid(cluster ~ .) + ylab(NULL) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels= c('0-9','11','12','13-14','16','20','24','24-60')) + ylim(-2,2) +
  theme(legend.position = "none",strip.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size = 9, color="black", angle = 45,hjust = 1),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size = 9),  axis.line =element_line(color="grey"),
        panel.grid.major = element_line(colour=NA),panel.grid.minor = element_line(colour="grey"),
        panel.background = element_rect(fill= "transparent", colour=NA),
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent",colour = NA))

p3 <- p3 + geom_text(data = dat_text, mapping = aes(x = Inf, y = Inf, label = label),hjust   = 2,  vjust   = 1.4,size=4)

for (i in 1:6) {
  datalist[[i]] <- as.data.frame(exon_total_toClust_scaled) %>%
